"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nBorn in a workhouse.  His father is missing from his birth certificate, which means that he was probably illegitimate.\n</p>\n</div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nElectrical Engineer\n</p>\n</div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nWilliam Albert Dickens - he was probably illegitimate, 3 surnames in his family - was brought up by his grandparents in Deal, (Kent). Went to his mother or his father, a butcher in London, when his Granddad died. Was William Morris until he needed  his birth certificate to marry &amp; found his name to be Dickens, he was the eldest.\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
